Students clutch resumes inside branded folders as event staff scan registrations and distribute tote bags filled with branded notebooks and pens at the entrance. Students engage with enthusiastic recruiters and attend workshops on networking etiquette, along with an alumni panel discussing technical interview preparation in an adjoining classroom. Career counselors provide guidance on professional interaction techniques, while international students queue for advice on visa sponsorship. As the day winds down, attendees fill interview sign-up sheets, and volunteers gather leftover brochures, while camera crews capture interviews. The aroma of coffee and catered snacks wafts from the lounge, enhancing the environment.

Students engaged with enthusiastic recruiters, using tablets at kiosks to upload resumes to the fair database and analyzing recruiter enthusiasm. An alumni panel discussed preparation for technical interviews, alongside workshops on networking etiquette in an adjoining classroom. A cybersecurity company ran a password-cracking challenge, while a robotics startup operated a small drone above its booth. As the day wound down, interview sign-up sheets filled with names, and announcement chimes signaled the final hour of the fair. Attendees, including international students who queued for visa sponsorship advice, left with tote bags filled with branded notebooks and business cards, and a post-event survey link flashed on the monitors near the exit.

The aroma of coffee and catered snacks wafts from the lounge, where alumni volunteers share encouraging messages, and camera crews capture interviews throughout the venue. As the day winds down, interview sign-up sheets fill with names, and volunteers begin gathering leftover brochures.

Inside, students, clutching resumes in branded folders, engage with enthusiastic recruiters in small groups, while career counselors assist those redirecting their focus toward applicable industries. The engineering society sponsors a resume review table near the stage, where recruiters distribute tote bags filled with branded notebooks and pens. Workshops on networking etiquette and an alumni panel discussing technical interview preparation occur in an adjoining classroom. As the day winds down, coffee and catered snacks fill the lounge, and the monitors flash a post-event survey link, with friends decompressing on the quad and comparing responses from companies.
